The following test-case also seems to be fixed by "[AA] Handle callbr instructions in alias analysis" (provided for future reference). The "call 0x2" disappears from the assembler output, likely because the compiler is not aware that the asm goto can modify the variable "a":

```
void foo (void) {
    int a = 1;
    asm goto ("call 0x0\n\t" : : "m" (a) : "memory" : next1);
next1:
  if (a) {
      asm volatile ("call 0x1\n\t");
  } else {
      asm volatile ("call 0x2\n\t");
  }
}
```

Another test-case provided for future reference:

```
/*
 * Breaks clang 12/13. I suspect that dead code elimination
 * removes the store to "head" because it is not aware of
 * asm goto. Seems to be fixed by
 * "[AA] Handle callbr instructions in alias analysis".
 */

void foo (void) {
  int *head;
  head = (void*)1;
  asm goto("ud2\n\t"::"m"(head):"memory":null);
null:
  return;
}
```
